snippet.textDisplay: Much more than a cry for help (in the narrow context of addiction, drug or otherwise), this song can be read as a realization of the bankruptcy of radical individualism. As much as we need to recognize our individuality, we have a deeper need to recognize that we cannot be entirely self-sufficient, that to be solipsistic is to be suicidal.
